Great Britain is an island in the North Atlantic Ocean off the
north-west coast of continental Europe, consisting of the countries
England, Scotland, and Wales. With an area of 209,331 km2 (80,823 sq mi),
it is the largest of the British Isles, the largest European island, and
the ninth-largest island in the world.[6][d] It is dominated by a maritime
climate with narrow temperature differences between seasons. The island
of Ireland, with an area 40 per cent that of Great Britain.